<subSubSection id="C37C5BEBFF93FFF0FF6A038832B5FEA9" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="350" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD90860FF93FFF1FF6A0388316DFDED" blockId="4.[166,1225,477,526]" box="[166,535,504,526]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
<geoCoordinate id="EE526EA7FF93FFF1FF6A03883256FDED" box="[166,300,504,526]" degrees="30" direction="east" minutes="25" orientation="longitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" precision="1" seconds="24.6" value="30.4235">30°25´24.6˝ E</geoCoordinate>
, 
<date id="FFD82EA0FF93FFF1FEFA038832E8FDED" box="[310,402,504,526]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" value="2003-06-04">4.06.2003</date>
(Nazarenko).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD90860FF93FFF1FF17005F37B2FD49" blockId="4.[166,1225,559,682]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
Labrum slightly sinuate at the middle of apex. Anterior margin of epipharynx with the sharp deep subrectangular central excision. Labral rods distinctly bordered at their inner sides, forming large sharp flattened subtriangular central cavity. 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FC7E001F308AFD73" box="[946,1008,623,656]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
Als 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF93FFF1FC1B00F2308AFD73" attach="left" box="[983,1008,642,656]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">1–3</subScript>
</emphasis>
of middle length, 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FF6A00E033AFFD4A" box="[166,213,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">ams</emphasis>
short and directed forward with 2 indistinct pits (sensillae?) located posteriorly in the
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF1958E8FF93FFF1FF6B04C131F9F901" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6453269" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6453269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6453269/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" startId="4.[167,200,1713,1735]" targetBox="[220,1179,724,1681]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BD90860FF93FFF1FF6B04C131F9F901" blockId="4.[166,1225,1713,1762]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
Fig. 4. Epipharynx of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6673E3FF93FFF1FEB504C23171F924" box="[377,523,1713,1735]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FEB504C232C5F924" box="[377,447,1714,1735]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">Hypera</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
: 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FDD804C231EBF924" box="[532,657,1713,1735]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
a — 
<taxonomicName id="4C6673E3FF93FFF1FD8F04C231EBF924" baseAuthorityName="Paykull" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[579,657,1713,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hypera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miles">H. miles</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FD5204C1300AF924" box="[670,880,1713,1735]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
b — 
<taxonomicName id="4C6673E3FF93FFF1FD0104C2300AF924" baseAuthorityName="Petri" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[717,880,1713,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hypera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transsylvanica">H. transsylvanica</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, general view; 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FBCE04C23771F924" box="[1026,1035,1714,1735]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">c</emphasis>
— the same, apical excision; 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FF3304BC32ABF901" box="[255,465,1740,1762]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
d — 
<taxonomicName id="4C6673E3FF93FFF1FEE104BC32ABF901" baseAuthorityName="Paykull" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[301,465,1740,1762]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Limobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borealis">Limobius borealis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. Scale bars 10 μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD90860FF93FFF1FF6A057130CCF8D2" blockId="4.[166,1225,1793,1841]" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
Рис. 4. Эпифаринкс некоторых видов рода 
<taxonomicName id="4C6673E3FF93FFF1FD91057131D8F8F5" box="[605,674,1793,1814]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hypera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FD91057131D8F8F5" box="[605,674,1793,1814]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">Hypera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FD610571305DF8F4" box="[685,807,1793,1815]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
a — 
<taxonomicName id="4C6673E3FF93FFF1FD160571305DF8F4" baseAuthorityName="Paykull" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[730,807,1793,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hypera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="miles">H. miles</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FCFE0571377BF8F4" box="[818,1025,1793,1815]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
b — 
<taxonomicName id="4C6673E3FF93FFF1FC930571377BF8F4" baseAuthorityName="Petri" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[863,1025,1793,1815]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Hypera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transsylvanica">H. transsylvanica</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, общий вид; 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FB44057137EBF8F5" box="[1160,1169,1793,1814]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">c</emphasis>
— то же, вершинная вырезка; 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF93FFF1FE68056B310FF8D2" box="[420,629,1819,1841]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="349">
d — 
<taxonomicName id="4C6673E3FF93FFF1FE1D056B310FF8D2" baseAuthorityName="Paykull" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[465,629,1819,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Limobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="349" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borealis">Limobius borealis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. Масштабные линейки 10 мкм.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD90860FF92FFF0FF6202DF32B5FEA9" blockId="5.[174,1233,175,330]" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
same excision with 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FE5502C032B2FF2A" box="[409,456,176,201]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">ams</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FE1402C0316AFF33" box="[472,528,176,208]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
Mes 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF92FFF0FDC402B2316AFF33" attach="left" box="[520,528,194,208]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
large, directed ventro-posteriad and located close together at the distal part of central cavity. 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FDAC02A031F6FF09" box="[608,652,208,234]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">Snp</emphasis>
posited posterolaterally of 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FC1302A0376EFF13" box="[991,1044,208,240]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
mes 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF92FFF0FBC00292376EFF13" attach="left" box="[1036,1044,226,240]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">1</subScript>
</emphasis>
at the sides of central depression and consisted of 4 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FDA002803101FEEA" box="[620,635,240,265]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">–</emphasis>
5 sensillae. 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FCCF02803041FEF3" box="[771,827,240,272]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">
Mes 
<subScript id="17E20A25FF92FFF0FCFF03723041FEF3" attach="left" box="[819,827,258,272]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
shorter and more slender, placed posteromedially of 
<emphasis id="B912D472FF92FFF0FE5D036032C3FECA" box="[401,441,272,297]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="350">snp</emphasis>
near the sides in central depression. Distal part of epipharynx with transverse toothed folds.
</paragraph>
